            <div class="col-sm">
                <h3>What is BOTOX®</h3>
                <p class="my-4">Botox is the botulinum toxin protein produced by the bacterium Clostridium botulinum. It prevents the release of the neurotransmitter acetylcholine causing a flaccid paralysis in and around the facial muscles that are injected. Botox treatment is used to treat a variety of muscular related medical conditions as well as cosmetically, to temporarily soften or completely eliminate facial wrinkles, frown lines, crows feet. </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="info-section py-120 pb0">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row align-items-center">
            <div class="col-sm">
                <h3>How Quickly Does BOTOX® Work?</h3>
                <p>You will start noticing decreased movement in your forehead and brow in 7 to 10 days and the full effect in 2 weeks. You will receive a follow up call from our office at 2 weeks to check on you and your results. The average person requires about 40 units of Botox to treat the forehead, glabella and crow’s feet. </p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-sm">
                <div class="image-space-main">
                    <img src="./images/botox-before-after.jpg" alt="Before and After Botox Treatment, which can take up to 2 weeks.">
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="content-single">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row align-items-center">
