                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-sm">
                <h3>What Medications and Supplements Should I Avoid Prior BOTOX® Treatment?</h3>
                <p class="my-4">Avoid common medications and supplements such as Aspirin, Excedrin, Ibuprofen, St Johns Wort, Omega Fatty Acids, Vitamin E, Ginko Biloboa, and Ginseng for at least 7 days prior to your treatment to reduce the chance of bleeding and bruising.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="info-section py-120 pb0">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row align-items-center">
            <div class="col-sm">
                <h3>What Are the Side Effects of BOTOX®?</h3>
                <p>
                    The side effects associated with this FDA approved cosmetic procedure may include pain, swelling and/or bruising at the injection site, and in some instances you may have a headache for a day or two. Less common complications include a droopy eyelid (ptosis), crooked smile or drooling, dry eyes or teary eyes.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Contraindications include pregnancy, breast feeding, neurological/neuromuscular disease or a known allergy to Botox.
                </p>
